        {
            "id": "eae4b8a681b841a8a5969",
            "questionText": "The astronomers observed a redshift in the hydrogen spectral line corresponding to the transition from energy level $!$n = 3$!$ to $!$n = 2$!$, and the observed wavelength of this line is $!$656.45 \\text{ nm}$!$. Assuming the hydrogen atom in the distant galaxy behaves according to the Bohr model, calculate the energy of the photon associated with this spectral line before redshift. Please provide the value of the redshift $!$z$!$ if known.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "2f8106ad192a42c089a79",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the formula that relates the emitted wavelength in a hydrogen atom transition. Select from the options below the formula that correctly represents the relation for the n = 3 to n = 2 transition using the Bohr model.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "516d8e51-d173-4735-85ca-b40323ce5f3c",
                        "39c26da9-7279-4edd-9cce-990d74d28d60"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\frac{1}{\\lambda} = R\\left(\\frac{1}{2^2} - \\frac{1}{3^2}\\right)$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\frac{1}{\\lambda} = R\\left(\\frac{1}{3^2} - \\frac{1}{2^2}\\right)$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = R\\left(\\frac{1}{2^2} - \\frac{1}{3^2}\\right)$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "94f1f041493c4d5099f10",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that you have the correct form, calculate the emitted wavelength $!$\\lambda_0$!$ using the relation. Remember that the Rydberg constant $!$R$!$ is approximately $!$1.097\\times10^{7}\\text{ m}^{-1}$!$. Provide the numerical value in meters.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "6.56e-7"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "516d8e51-d173-4735-85ca-b40323ce5f3c"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "b33f83890d744a24b8973",
                    "stepText": "Now, identify the correct formula that expresses the energy of a photon in terms of its wavelength. Choose the option that correctly links $!$E$!$, $!$h$!$, $!$c$!$, and $!$\\lambda$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "6c8fd7e5-446f-44d0-87f4-63ad0de73b9e",
                        "114913f7-42e4-4f1e-a164-563a0df26437"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$E = \\frac{hc}{\\lambda}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$E = h\\lambda c$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$E = \\frac{\\lambda}{hc}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "738de79841e344509f98e",
                    "stepText": "Excellent. Using the value of $!$\\lambda_0$!$ you computed and the constants $!$h = 6.626\\times10^{-34}\\text{ J \\cdot s}$!$ and $!$c = 3.00\\times10^{8}\\text{ m/s}$!$, calculate the energy $!$E$!$ of the photon in joules.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "3.03e-19"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "J",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "6c8fd7e5-446f-44d0-87f4-63ad0de73b9e"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "f0d5086aa7f14e6f89eb4",
                    "stepText": "Next, determine which formula correctly defines the redshift $!$z$!$ in terms of the observed wavelength $!$\\lambda_{obs}$!$ and the emitted wavelength $!$\\lambda_0$!$. Choose the appropriate option.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
